obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (8054)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8054&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Bihar and Uttar Pradesh (Alteration of Boundaries)`
  line `Act, 1968.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (8055)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. 10th June, 1970, vide notification No. G.S.R. 901, dated 9th June, 1970, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8055&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day^1`
  line `" means the day which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint;`
  line
  line `(b) "assembly constituency", "council constituency" and "parliamentary constituency" have the`
  line `same meanings as in the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(c) "deep stream", in relation to the river Ganga or the river Ghaghra, means the deep stream`
  line `thereof as verified and agreed upon by the State Governments of Bihar and Uttar Pradesh after the`
  line `30th day of September of the year preceding the year in which the appointed day falls and before the`
  line `1st day of January of the year in which the appointed day falls and in default of agreement`
  line `between the State Governments, as determined by such authority as may be specified by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) "fixed boundary" means the boundary line demarcated under the provisions of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 3 in relation to the river Ganga or the river Ghaghra, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(e) "law" includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme,`
  line `notification or other instrument having the force of law in the whole or in any part of the State of`
  line `Bihar or Uttar Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(f) "notified order" means an order published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "sitting member", in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislature of a State,`
  line `means a person who immediately before the appointed day is a member of that House;`
  line
  line `(i) "transferred territories" means,—`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to the State of Bihar, the territories transferred by this Act from that State to the`
  line `State of Uttar Pradesh, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to the State of Uttar Pradesh, the territories transferred by this Act from that`
  line `State to the State of Bihar;`
  line
  line `(j) any reference to a district of a State shall be construed as a reference to the area physically`
  line `comprised within that district immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (8056)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Transfer of territories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8056&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day,--`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be added to the State of Bihar--`
  line
  line `(i) all the territories of Ballia district of the State of Uttar Pradesh lying between the fixed`
  line `boundary and the deep stream of the river Ghaghra, and`
  line
  line `(ii) all the territories of that district lying between the fixed boundary and the deep stream of`
  line `the river Ganga,`
  line
  line `and the said territories shall thereupon cease to form part of the State of Uttar Pradesh; and`
  line
  line `(b) there shall be added to the State of Uttar Pradesh--`
  line
  line `(i) all the territories of Saran district of the State of Bihar lying between the fixed boundary`
  line `and the deep stream of the river Ghaghra, and`
  line
  line `(ii) all the territories of Shahabad district of the State of Bihar lying between the fixed`
  line `boundary and the deep stream of the river Ganga,`
  line
  line `and the said territories shall thereupon cease to form part of the State of Bihar.`
  line
  line `(2) The fixed boundary in relation to each of the rivers Ganga and Ghaghra shall be demarcated by an`
  line `authority appointed in this behalf by the Central Government so as to be generally in conformity with the`
  line `boundary line described in the Schedule in relation to that river:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the process of such demarcation, the said authority shall have power to rationalise to`
  line `the extent considered necessary by him, the boundary alignment between the high banks of the river`
  line `Ganga or the river Ghaghra, as the case may be, and in particular shall try--`
  line
  line `(a) to ensure, as far as possible, the stability of the boundary pillars and the recognition of the`
  line `boundary alignment both during the dry and flood seasons; and`
  line
  line `(b) to avoid, as far as possible, the splitting up of the existing abadis.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of such demarcation,--`
  line
  line `(a) the decision of the said authority on any matter relating to the interpretation of any part of the`
  line `description of the boundary given in the Schedule (including the determination of the relevant record`
  line `referred to in the Explanatory Note to the Schedule) shall be final;`
  line
  line `(b) the said authority shall have power to determine the location of the points at which the`
  line `boundary pillars shall be constructed and to specify the State Government which shall be responsible`
  line `for the construction and maintenance of the boundary pillars at such points according to such`
  line `specifications as that authority may indicate (the pillars of the same specifications being apportioned,`
  line `as far as practicable equally between the two State Governments), the decision of the said authority in`
  line `regard to these matters being final;`
  line
  line `(c) it shall be lawful for the said authority and for any person specified by such authority to enter`
  line `upon and survey any area in the vicinity of the boundary line and to do all other acts as may be`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(4) The authority referred to in sub-section (2) shall also prepare a map of the transferred territories`
  line showing--
  line
  line `(a) the deep stream of the river Ghaghra or the river Ganga, as the case may be, and the fixed`
  line `boundary in relation to that river;`
  line
  line `(b) the names and boundaries of the villages in the transferred territories, as indicated by the`
  line `State Government having jurisdiction over the territories before their transfer, with reference to the`
  line `revenue records of that Government in force immediately before the preparation of such map,`
  line
  line `and forward such map to the Central Government who shall cause it to be published in the transferred`
  line `territories in such manner as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(5) As from the appointed day, the State Government of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh shall, by order in the`
  line `Official Gazette, provide for the administration of the territories transferred to that State under`
  line `sub-section (1) by including them or any part of them in such district, sub-division, police-station or other`
  line `administrative unit as may be specified in the order`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (8057)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Amendment of First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8057&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, under the heading "I. THE STATES"—`
  line
  line `(a) for the entry against "3. Bihar", the following shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"The territories which immediately before the commencement of this Constitution were either`
  line `comprised in the Province of Bihar or were being administered as if they formed part of that`
  line `Province and the territories specified in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Bihar and`
  line `Uttar Pradesh (Alteration of Boundaries) Act, 1968, but excluding the territories specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Bihar and West Bengal (Transfer of Territories) Act, 1956, and`
  line `the territories specified in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 3 of the first mentioned Act.";`
  line
  line `(b) for the entry against "13. Uttar Pradesh", the following shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"The territories which immediately before the commencement of this Constitution were either`
  line `comprised in the Province known as the United Provinces or were being administered as if they`
  line `formed part of that Province and the territories specified in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3 of the Bihar and Uttar Pradesh (Alteration of Boundaries) Act, 1968, but excluding the`
  line `territories specified in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 3 of that Act."`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (8058)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Construction of Delimitation Orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8058&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, any reference in any order`
  line `relating to delimitation of parliamentary constituencies, assembly constituencies or council`
  line constituencies—
  line
  line `(a) (i) to the State of Bihar, shall be construed as including the territories transferred to that State`
  line `from the State of Uttar Pradesh under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 3, but excluding the`
  line `territories transferred from the State of Bihar to the State of Uttar Pradesh under clause (b) of that`
  line sub-section;
  line
  line `(ii) to any district, sub-division, police-station or other administrative unit in the State of Bihar,`
  line `shall be construed as including that part of the territories, if any, transferred to that State, which is`
  line `included in that district, sub-division, police-station or other administrative unit by order made under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) (i) to the State of Uttar Pradesh, shall be construed as including the territories transferred to`
  line `that State from the State of Bihar under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 3, but excluding the`
  line `territories transferred from the State of Uttar Pradesh to the State of Bihar under clause (a) of that`
  line sub-section;
  line
  line `(ii) to any district, sub-division, police-station or other administrative unit in the State of`
  line `Uttar Pradesh, shall be construed as including that part of the territories, if any, transferred to that`
  line `State, which is included in that district, sub-division, police-station or other administrative unit by`
  line `order made under sub-section (5) of section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (8059)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Provision as to sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8059&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every sitting member of the House of the People`
  line `representing any parliamentary constituency the extent of which has been altered by virtue of the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall, notwithstanding such alteration, be deemed, as from the appointed day, to`
  line `have been elected to that House by that constituency as so altered`
  line
  line `(2) Every sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of the State of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh`
  line `representing any assembly constituency the extent of which has been altered by virtue of the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall, notwithstanding such alteration, be deemed as from the appointed day, to have been elected`
  line `to the said Legislative Assembly by that constituency as so altered.`
  line
  line `(3) Every sitting member of the Legislative Council of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh representing any`
  line `council constituency the extent of which has been altered by virtue of the provisions of this Act, shall,`
  line `notwithstanding such alteration, be deemed as from the appointed day, to have been elected to the said`
  line `Legislative Council by that constituency as so altered.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (8060)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Extension of jurisdiction of, and transfer of proceedings to, High Court at Patna.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8060&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except`
  line `as hereinafter provided—`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the High Court at Patna shall, as from the appointed day, extend to the`
  line `territories transferred by this Act from the State of Uttar Pradesh to the State of Bihar; and`
  line
  line `(b) the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad shall, as from that day, have no jurisdiction in`
  line `respect of the said territories.`
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad immediately before the`
  line `appointed day as are certified by the Chief Justice of that High Court, having regard to the place of`
  line `accrual of the cause of action and other circumstances, to be proceedings which ought to be heard and`
  line `decided by the High Court at Patna shall, as soon as may be after such certification, be transferred to the`
  line `High Court at Patna.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), but save as hereinafter provided,`
  line `the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad shall have, and the High Court at Patna shall not have,`
  line `jurisdiction to entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to appear to the Supreme Court`
  line `applications for review and other proceedings, where any such proceedings seek any relief in respect of`
  line `any order passed by the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad before the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, after such proceedings have been entertained by the High Court of Judicature at`
  line `Allahabad, it appears to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the`
  line `High Court at Patna, he shall order that they shall be so transferred and such proceedings shall thereupon`
  line `be transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad—`
  line
  line `(a) before the appointed day in any proceedings transferred to the High Court at Patna by virtue`
  line `of sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad retains`
  line `jurisdiction by virtue of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall, for all purposes, have effect not only as an order of the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad, but`
  line `also as an order made by the High Court at Patna.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to any rule made or direction given by the High Court at Patna, any such person who`
  line `immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of Judicature at`
  line `Allahabad as may be specified in this behalf by the Chief Justice of the High Court at Patna having regard`
  line `to the transfer of territories from the State of Uttar Pradesh to the State of Bihar, shall be recognised as an`
  line `advocate entitled to practise in the High Court at Patna.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (8061)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Extension of jurisdiction of, and transfer of proceedings to, High Court at Allahabad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8061&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as hereinafter provided—`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad shall, as from the appointed day,`
  line `extend to the territories transferred by this Act from the State of Bihar to the State of Uttar Pradesh;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the High Court at Patna shall, as from that day, have no jurisdiction in respect of the said`
  line territories.
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the High Court at Patna immediately before the appointed day as are`
  line `certified by the Chief Justice of that High Court, having regard to the place of accrual of the cause of`
  line `action and other circumstances, to be proceedings which ought to be heard and decided by the High Court`
  line `of Judicature at Allahabad shall, as soon as may be after such certification, be transferred to the`
  line `High Court of Judicature at Allahabad.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), but save as hereinafter provided,`
  line `the High Court at Patna shall have, and the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad shall not have,`
  line `jurisdiction to entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court,`
  line `applications for review and other proceedings, where any such proceedings seek any relief in respect of`
  line `any order passed by the High Court at Patna before the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, after such proceedings have been entertained by the High Court at Patna, it appears`
  line `to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High Court of Judicature at`
  line `Allahabad, he shall order that they shall be so transferred and such proceedings shall thereupon be`
  line `transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the High Court at Patna—`
  line
  line `(a) before the appointed day in any proceedings transferred to the High Court of Judicature at`
  line `Allahabad by virtue of sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court at Patna retains jurisdiction by virtue`
  line `of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall, for all purposes, have effect not only as an order of the High Court at Patna, but also as an order`
  line `made by the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to any rule made or direction given by the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad, any`
  line `such person who immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise in the`
  line `High Court at Patna as may be specified in this behalf by the Chief Justice of the High Court of Judicature`
  line `at Allahabad having regard to the transfer of territories from the State of Bihar to the State of Uttar`
  line `Pradesh, shall be recognised as an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of Judicature at`
  line Allahabad.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (8062)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Right to appear in any proceedings transferred under section 7 or section 8.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8062&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Any person who`
  line `immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court at Patna or the`
  line `High Court of Judicature at Allahabad and was authorised to appear in any proceedings transferred under`
  line `section 7 or section 8 shall have the right to appear in the High Court to which the proceedings have been`
  line `transferred, in relation to those proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (8063)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8063&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of sections 7 and 8,—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in the High Court at Patna or the High Court of`
  line `Judicature at Allahabad until that Court has disposed of all issues between the parties, including any`
  line `issue with respect to the taxation of the costs of the proceedings and shall include appeals,`
  line `applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for review, petitions for revision`
  line `and petitions for writs;`
  line
  line `(b) references to the High Court at Patna or the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad shall be`
  line `construed as including references to a Judge or division court thereof, and references to an order made`
  line `by a court or a Judge shall be construed as including references to a sentence, judgment or decree`
  line `passed or made by that court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (8064)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Appropriation of moneys for expenditure in transferred territories under existing appropriation Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8064&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day, any Act passed by the Legislature of the State of`
  line `Bihar or Uttar Pradesh before that day for the appropriation of any moneys out of the Consolidated Fundof the State to meet any expenditure in respect of any part of the financial year in which the appointed day`
  line `falls shall have effect also in relation to the territories transferred to that State by the provisions of Part II`
  line `and it shall be lawful for the State Government to spend any amount in those territories out of the amount`
  line `authorised by such Act to be expended for any service in that State.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governor of Bihar or of Uttar Pradesh may, after the appointed day, authorise such`
  line `expenditure, from the Consolidated Fund of the State as he deems necessary for any purpose or service in`
  line `the territories transferred to that State for a period of not more than six months beginning with the`
  line `appointed day pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislature of the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (8065)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Reports relating to accounts of Bihar and Uttar Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8065&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The reports of the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India referred to in clause (2) of article 151 of the Constitution relating to the accounts`
  line `of the State of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh in respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be`
  line `submitted to the Governor of each of the States of Bihar and Uttar Pradesh who shall cause them to be`
  line `laid before the Legislature of the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (8066)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Land and goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8066&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Part, all land and all stores, articles`
  line `and other goods belonging to the State of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh in the transferred territories shall, as`
  line `from the appointed day, pass to the State to which the territories are transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) In this section, the expression "land" includes immovable property of every kind and any rights in`
  line `or over such property.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (8067)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Arrears of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8067&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The right of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh to recover arrears of any tax or duty on`
  line `property situate in the transferred territories, including land revenue, or to recover arrears of any other tax`
  line `or duty in any case where the place of assessment of that tax or duty is in the transferred territories shall`
  line `belong to the State to which the territories are transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (8068)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Right to recover loans and advances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8068&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The right to recover any loans or advances made before`
  line `the appointed day by Bihar or Uttar Pradesh to any local body, society, agriculturist, or other person in the`
  line `transferred territories shall belong to the State to which the territories are transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (8069)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Refund of taxes collected in excess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8069&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The liability of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh to refund any tax or`
  line `duty on property situate in the transferred territories, including land revenue, collected in excess shall be`
  line `the liability of the State to which the territories are transferred and the liability of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh`
  line `to refund any other tax or duty collected in excess in any case where the place of assessment of the tax or`
  line `duty is in the transferred territories shall also be the liability of the State to which the territories are`
  line transferred.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (8070)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title Deposits.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8070&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The liability of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh in respect of any civil deposit or local fund`
  line `deposit made in the transferred territories shall, as from the appointed day, be the liability of the State to`
  line `which the territories are transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (8071)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Contracts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8071&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, before the appointed day, the State of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh has made`
  line `any contract in the exercise of its executive power for any purposes of the State, that contract shall be`
  line `deemed to have been made in the exercise of the executive power—`
  line
  line `(a) if such purposes are, as from that day, purposes relatable exclusively to the transferred`
  line `territories, of the State to which the territories are transferred; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, of the State which made the contract, and all rights and liabilities which`
  line `have accrued, or may accrue, under any such contract shall, to the extent to which they are rights or`
  line `liabilities of the State which made the contract, be rights or liabilities of the State specified in`
  line `clause (a) or clause (b) above`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, there shall be deemed to be included in the liabilities which have`
  line `accrued or may accrue under any contract—`
  line
  line `(a) any liability to satisfy an order or award made by any court or other tribunal in proceedings`
  line `relating to the contract; and`
  line
  line `(b) any liability in respect of expenses incurred in or in connection with any such proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall have effect subject to the other provisions of this Part relating to the`
  line `apportionment of liabilities in respect of loans, guarantees and other financial obligations`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (8072)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Liability in respect of actionable wrong.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8072&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the`
  line `State of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh is subject to any liability in respect of an actionable wrong, other than`
  line `breach of contract, that liability shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the cause of action arose wholly within the transferred territories, be a liability of the State`
  line `to which the territories are transferred; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, continue to be a liability of the State which, immediately before that day,`
  line `was subject to such liability`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (8073)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Liability as guarantor of co-operative societies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8073&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed`
  line `day, the State of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh is liable as guarantor in respect of any liability of a registered`
  line `co-operative society, that liability shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the area of the society's operations is limited to the transferred territories, be a liability of`
  line `the State to which the territories are transferred; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, continue to be a liability of the State which, immediately before that day,`
  line `was subject to such liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (8074)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Items in suspense.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8074&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `If any item in suspense is ultimately found to affect an asset or liability of`
  line `the nature referred to in any of the foregoing provisions of this Part, it shall be dealt with in accordance`
  line `with that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (8075)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Apportionment of assets or liabilities by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8075&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Where the States of Bihar and`
  line `Uttar Pradesh agree that the benefit or burden of any particular asset or liability should be apportioned`
  line `between them in a manner other than that provided for in the foregoing provisions of this Part, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained therein, the benefit or burden of that asset or liability shall be`
  line `apportioned in the manner agreed upon.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (8076)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of Central Government to order allocation or adjustment in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8076&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line Where,
  line `by virtue of any of the provisions of this Part, either of the States of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh becomes`
  line `entitled to any property or obtains any benefits or becomes subject to any liability, and the`
  line `Central Government, on a reference made within a period of three years from the appointed day by either`
  line `of the States, is of opinion that it is just and equitable that that property or those benefits should be`
  line `transferred to, or shared with, the other State or that a contribution towards that liability should be made`
  line `by the other State, the said property or benefits shall be allocated in such manner between the two States,`
  line `or the other State shall make to the State subject to the liability such contribution in respect thereof, as the`
  line `Central Government may, after consultation with the two State Governments, by order determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (8077)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Expenditure to be charged on the Consolidated Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8077&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `All sums payable by either Bihar or`
  line `Uttar Pradesh to the other State by virtue of the provisions of this Part shall be charged on the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of the State by which such sums are payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (8078)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `State Financial Corporations and State Electricity Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8078&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day—`
  line
  line `(a) the Financial Corporations constituted under the State Financial Corporations`
  line `Act, 1951 (63 of 1951), for the States of Bihar and Uttar Pradesh, and`
  line
  line `(b) the State Electricity Boards constituted under the Electricity (Supply) Act, 1948 (54 of 1948),`
  line `for the said States,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to have been constituted for those States with their areas as altered by the provisions of`
  line `section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (8079)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Territorial extent of laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8079&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 3 shall not be deemed to have effected any`
  line `change in the territories to which any law in force immediately before the appointed day extends or`
  line `applies, and territorial references in any such law to the State of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh shall, until`
  line `otherwise provided by a competent Legislature or other competent authority, be construed as meaning the`
  line `territories within that State immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (8080)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to adapt laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8080&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of facilitating the application of any law in relation to the`
  line `State of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh, the appropriate Government may, before the expiration of one year from`
  line `the appointed day, by order make such adaptations and modifications of the law, whether by way of`
  line `repeal or amendment as may be necessary or expedient, and thereupon every such law shall have effect`
  line `subject to the adaptations or modifications so made until altered, repealed or amended by a competent`
  line `Legislature or other competent authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "appropriate Government" means as respects any law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List, the Central Government, and as respects any other law,`
  line `the State Government`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (8081)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8081&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has been`
  line `made for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal or authority, required`
  line `or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its application in relation to the`
  line `State of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh, construe the law in such manner, without affecting the substance, as may`
  line `be necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (8082)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8082&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the State of Bihar or`
  line `Uttar Pradesh is a party to any legal proceedings with respect to any property, rights or liabilities`
  line `transferred to the other State under this Act, the other State shall be deemed to be substituted for the State`
  line `from which such property rights or liabilities are transferred as a party to those proceedings, or added as a`
  line `party thereto, as the case may be, and the proceedings may continue accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (8083)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8083&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before a court (other than a High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area which on`
  line `that day falls within the State of Bihar or Uttar Pradesh shall, if it is a proceeding relatable exclusively to`
  line `any part of the territories which as from that day are the territories of the other State, stand transferred to`
  line `the corresponding court, tribunal authority or officer in the other State.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under sub-section (1),`
  line `it shall be referred to the High Court having jurisdiction in respect of the area in which the court, tribunal,`
  line `authority or officer before which, or before whom, such proceeding is pending on the appointed day, is`
  line `functioning, and the decision of that High Court shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "proceeding" includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) "corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer" in a State means—`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in which, or before whom, the proceeding would`
  line `have lain if the proceeding had been instituted after the appointed day, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority or officer in that State as may be`
  line `determined after the appointed day by the Government of that State, or before the appointed day`
  line `by the Government of the other State, to be the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (8084)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Right of pleaders to practise in certain courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8084&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, is enrolled as a pleader entitled to practise in any subordinate courts in the transferred`
  line `territories shall, for a period of six months from that day, continue to be entitled to practise in those courts, notwithstanding that the whole or any part of the territories within the jurisdiction of those courts`
  line `has been transferred to another State.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (8085)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Construction of boundary pillars, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8085&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be lawful for the State Government which is`
  line `responsible for the construction of any boundary pillar under sub-section (3) of section 3 to cause such`
  line `pillar to be constructed and maintained and no suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against`
  line `the State Government or any of its officers for anything in good faith done or intended to be done under`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The boundary pillars shall be inspected jointly by the officers of the State Governments of Bihar`
  line `and Uttar Pradesh in accordance with such rules as the Central Government may make in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever wilfully removes or injures any boundary pillar shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), an`
  line `offence under sub-section (3) may be inquired into and tried by a court in either of the States of Bihar and`
  line `Uttar Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (8086)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Validity of demarcation done before commencement of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8086&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `All things done, and all steps`
  line `taken, before the commencement of this Act in connection with the demarcation of the fixed boundary in`
  line `relation to the river Ganga or the river Ghaghra, as the case may be, shall, in so far as they are in`
  line `conformity with the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 3, be deemed to have been done in`
  line `accordance with law.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (8087)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Effect of provisions inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8087&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding any law, custom or usage which is inconsistent therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (8088)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8088&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the President may, by notified order, do anything, not inconsistent with such provisions which`
  line `appears to him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (8089)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1986)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543&sectionId=8089&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00007_196824_1517807318543
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or ^1`
  line `[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
